<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-15T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1291: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-15T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            15, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:15
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>15. Chinese Government is considering taking over full control of
                                Chinese Eastern Railway retaining Stevens and selected staff. To
                                accomplish this financial assistance will be necessary. Shall I
                                encourage Chinese to take this step? Can I give them any assurance
                                of financial assistance?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>